ough this complex new religious terrain. Basing his discussion on interviews with militant activists and case studies of rebellious movements, Juergensmeyer puts a human face on conflicts that have become increasingly abstract. He revises our notions of religious revolution and offers positive proposals for responding to religious activism in ways that will diminish the violence and lead to an accommodation between radical religion and the secular world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRadicalismxReligious aspects. 0aReligions. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh  a21st century.  aactivism.  aactivist.  aactivists.  aal qaeda.  abelief.  achristian.  achristianity.  acold war.  afaith.  ainsurgency.  ainsurgents.  airaq.  aislam.  amilitary.  amilitia.  anationalism.  apolitical rebellion.  apolitical.  apolitics.  aradical religion.  areligion.  areligious activism.  areligious nationalism.  areligious rebellion.  areligious studies.  asecular world.  asecular.  atrue story.  aturn of the century.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025554840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093476440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520934764423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520934764/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY